name: HealthCare_DataSet (1).pdf
content: Patient 1: Alice Smith, born on March 22, 1975, with medical record number 10001, has a past history of hypertension and hyperlipidemia and underwent a cholecystectomy in 2010. She presented with abdominal pain for two days. She was diagnosed with gastroenteritis and prescribed Ondansetron, with a follow-up scheduled in five days. Her complete blood count was 13.0 g/dL, glucose 102 mg/dL, and creatinine 1.0 mg/dL as of September 15, 2023. She takes Metformin 500 mg twice daily and Lisinopril 10 mg once daily. She is allergic to penicillin and NSAIDs. Her vitals on presentation were 135/85 mmHg blood pressure, pulse 78 bpm, and temperature 99.0°F. Patient 2: Bob Johnson, born on July 11, 1982, medical record number 10002, has a history of asthma with no prior surgeries. He reported shortness of breath for a week. Diagnosed with an asthma exacerbation, he was prescribed an Albuterol inhaler as needed and asked to follow up in a week. His lab results included a hemoglobin of 14.2 g/dL, glucose 90 mg/dL, and creatinine 0.8 mg/dL. He has a sulfonamide allergy, and his vitals were 128/82 mmHg, pulse 88 bpm, and temperature 98.4°F. Patient 3: Carol Williams, born December 5, 1969, medical record number 10003, has diabetes and osteoarthritis, and underwent a knee replacement in 2015. She complained of knee pain for two weeks and was diagnosed with an osteoarthritis flare. Ibuprofen was prescribed, with follow-up in two weeks. Her labs showed hemoglobin 12.8 g/dL, glucose 110 mg/dL, and creatinine 0.9 mg/dL. She takes Metformin 500 mg twice daily and has no known allergies. Her blood pressure was 142/88 mmHg, pulse 80 bpm, and temperature 98.7°F. Patient 4: David Brown, born May 19, 1990, medical record number 10004, has hypertension and underwent a tonsillectomy in 2000. He presented with dizziness for three days and was diagnosed with vertigo. Meclizine was prescribed with a follow-up in a week. His labs revealed hemoglobin 13.5 g/dL, glucose 98 mg/dL, and creatinine 1.0 mg/dL. He takes Lisinopril 10 mg daily and is allergic to penicillin. Vitals were 138/86 mmHg, pulse 82 bpm, and temperature 98.6°F. Patient 5: Emily Davis, born September 28, 1985, medical record number 10005, has diabetes and hypothyroidism, with a history of C-section in 2012. She reported fatigue for two weeks and was diagnosed with hypothyroidism. Levothyroxine was prescribed, and she was asked to follow up in four weeks. Her hemoglobin was 12.4 g/dL, glucose 95 mg/dL, and creatinine 0.9 mg/dL. She takes Metformin 500 mg twice daily and has a sulfonamide allergy. Her vitals were 130/85 mmHg, pulse 76 bpm, and temperature 98.5°F. Patient 6: Frank Miller, born January 17, 1978, medical record number 10006, has hypertension and hyperlipidemia, and underwent hernia repair in 2008. He presented with chest discomfort for one day and was diagnosed with angina. Nitroglycerin was prescribed as needed, with a follow-up in one week.
